label.value: ChIP-chip by tiling array design

definition.value: A study design which aims to identify protein binding sites in genomic DNA by a combination of chromatin immunoprecipitation and tiling microarray (chip) assays.

label.value: dose response design

definition.value: A study design that examines the relationship between the size of the administered dose and the extent of the response.

label.value: ChIP-chip by tiling array assay

definition.value: A ChIP-ChIP assay in which immunoprecipitated chromatin is run on a tiling array that covers stretches of DNA to to detect which elements in those stretches are present in the isolated chromatin

label.value: epitope specific helper T cell enhancement of T cell mediated immune response

definition.value: A process of helper T cell enhancement of T cell mediated immune response resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: epitope specific interferon-beta production by T cells

definition.value: A process of interferon-beta production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: organism part comparison design

definition.value: A study design that compares tissues, regions, organs within or between organisms

label.value: intracellular material detection measuring epitope specific granzyme B release by T cells

definition.value: A flow cytometry assay that detects epitope specific granzyme B release by T cells

label.value: protein binding site identification design

definition.value: A study design that investigates protein binding sites on nucleic acids.

label.value: sex comparison design

definition.value: A study design that assays differences associated with an organism's sex, gender or mating type.

label.value: transcription profiling by tiling array design

definition.value: A study design in which gene expression on a genome-wide basis is evaluated, without bias toward coding or noncoding regions, using tiling arrays containing oligonucleotides that are either overlapping or spaced at regular intervals.

label.value: cell differentiation design

definition.value: A study design that assays events associated with cell development or differentiation.

label.value: transcription profiling design

definition.value: A study design that identifies forms and abundance of transcripts in the genome.

label.value: operon identification design

definition.value: A study design that identifies locations and members of operons in a genome.

label.value: radio immuno assay measuring epitope specific interferon-gamma production by T cells

definition.value: A radio immuno assay that detects interferon-gamma production by T cells.

label.value: DNA methylation profiling by high throughput sequencing design

definition.value: A study design in which the methylation state of DNA is determined and is compared between samples using high throughput sequencing technology.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific granzyme B release by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytotoxic T cell degranulation assay that detects granzyme B release by T cells.

label.value: intracellular cytokine staining assay measuring epitope specific chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 9 production by T cells

definition.value: A flow cytometry assay that detects chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 9 production by T cells.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific macrophage inflammatory protein-1 gamma production by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay that detects macrophage inflammatory protein-1 gamma production by T cells.

label.value: epitope specific chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 9 production by T cells

definition.value: A process of chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 9 production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: all pairs design

definition.value: A study design in which all specimens are compared to every other specimen.

label.value: proteomic profiling by array design

definition.value: A study design in which proteins in a sample are detected, quantified or otherwise analysed, through an array-based technology.

label.value: q-value

definition.value:
A quantitative confidence value that measures the minimum false discovery rate that is incurred when calling that test significant. 
To compute q-values, it is necessary to know the p-value produced by a test and possibly set a false discovery rate level.

label.value: genotyping design

definition.value: A study design that classifies an individual or group of individuals on the basis of alleles, haplotypes, SNPs.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-2 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-2 production by T cells.

label.value: epitope specific interleukin-15 production by T cells

definition.value: A process of interleukin-15 production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: epitope specific macrophage inflammatory protein-1 gamma production by T cells

definition.value: A process of macrophage inflammatory protein-1 gamma production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: individual genetic characteristics comparison design

definition.value: A study design where genotype, haplotype, or other individual genetic characteristics are compared.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-1 beta production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-1 beta production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-4 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-4 production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-6 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-6 production by T cells.

label.value: cell culture analyte detection bioassay measuring epitope specific tumor necrosis factor alpha production by T cells

definition.value: A reporter cell line analyte detection bioassay that detects tumor necrosis factor alpha production by T cells.

label.value: intracellular cytokine staining assay measuring epitope specific lymphotoxin A production by T cells

definition.value: A flow cytometry assay that detects lymphotoxin A production by T cells.

label.value: pathogenicity design

definition.value: A study design in which an infective agent such as a bacterium, virus, protozoan, fungus etc. infects a host organism(s) and the infective agent is assayed.

label.value: ELISPOT assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-5 production by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunospot assay that detects interleukin-5 production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific macrophage inflammatory protein-1 gamma production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects macrophage inflammatory protein-1 gamma production by T cells.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-8 production by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects interleukin-8 production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 9 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 9 production by T cells.

label.value: genetic modification design

definition.value: A study design in which an organism(s) is studied that has had genetic material removed, rearranged, mutagenized or added, such as in a knock out.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific granzyme B release by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay that detects epitope specific granzyme B release by T cells.

label.value: epitope specific IP-10 production by T cells

definition.value: A process of IP-10 production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: transcription profiling by array assay

definition.value: A transcription profiling assay that uses array technology.

label.value: strain comparison design

definition.value: A study design that assays differences between multiple strains, cultivars, serovars, isolates, lines from organisms of a single species.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific monocyte chemotactic protein-1 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects monocyte chemotactic protein-1 production by T cells.

label.value: intracellular cytokine staining assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-12 production by T cells

definition.value: A flow cytometry assay that detects interleukin-12 production by T cells.

label.value: in vivo assay measuring T cell epitope specific disease exacerbation

definition.value: An efficacy of T cell epitope intervention experiment that uses a disease exacerbation in vivo intervention experiment.

label.value: cell specimen

definition.value: A specimen primarily composed of a cell or cells collected from a multicellular organism or a cell culture.

label.value: monospecific T cell recognition assay measuring MHC ligand processing and presentation

definition.value: A MHC ligand processing and presentation assay in which the presence of a specific ligand in an eluate is detected using the response of T cells that are known to be monospecific for that ligand as a readout.

label.value: epitope specific interleukin-17F production by T cells

definition.value: A process of interleukin-17F production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

definition.value: An epitope specific immune intervention in which the induced response targets a T cell epitope

label.value: specimen with known storage state

definition.value: A specimen for which it is known whether it has been subjected to storage of a specified type.
